Halong Bay Violet Cruise - Terrible!!
Mar 2012 ‚Ä¢ Couples
Was convinced by travel agent to book on this junk which was described as most luxurious in Halong Bay. Booked a suite, but mix up with booking ended up with a deluxe cabin - big mistake. The cabin was all differing shades of brown with very stained and damaged yellow curtains. The sofa had cigarette burns in despite the boat being non-smoking. The private balcony attached to the cabin also opened on to the wheelhouse, so there were sailors and the captain talking at all hours so no privacy! Also the doors to the balcony did not lock so no security either.
The food onboard was the highlight, only problem is that it took ages to arrive once ordered. The tables in the dining room/reception area/bar were also very close together so no chance of a private conversation here either. The staff were nice, but a bit in your face. Very expensive for 1 night over US$650, not worth the money. Would not reccommend this cruise.
p.s. If you do cruise, make sure your cabin safe works. One couple onboard had a suite with a safe that didn't, long story short, they came back on shore a couple of hundred dollars lighter. Management refused to take resposibility because they didn't put their money in the safe!!
p.p.s. In your cabin you will find two pairs of flip-flops to use while onboard, whatever you do, do not take them home with you. Two ladies onboard did and they were made to open their luggage and return them before they were able to leave the boat. Obviously they re-use their flip flops!! Verruca alert!!
